hands_on_practices.solution:
We start from the Friedmann equation for a flat universe with matter and radiation,
$$\biggl(\frac{\dot a}{a}\biggr)^2 = H_0^2\bigl(\Omega_{m,0}a^{-3} + \Omega_{r,0}a^{-4}\bigr)\,. $$

1. Find the scale factor at equality $a_{eq}$ by solving $\rho_m=\rho_r$:
$$\rho_{m,0}a^{-3}=\rho_{r,0}a^{-4}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
a_{eq}=\frac{\rho_{r,0}}{\rho_{m,0}}
=\frac{\Omega_{r,0}}{\Omega_{m,0}}\,. $$

2. The cosmic time as a function of $a$ is
$$t(a)=\int_0^a\frac{da'}{\dot a'}
=\frac1{H_0}\int_0^a\frac{da'}{a'\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}a'^{-3}+\Omega_{r,0}a'^{-4}}}\,. $$

3. Simplify the integrand:
$$\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}a'^{-3}+\Omega_{r,0}a'^{-4}}
=a'^{-2}\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}a'+\Omega_{r,0}}\,, $$
so
$$t(a)=\frac1{H_0}\int_0^a\frac{a'\,da'}{\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}a'+\Omega_{r,0}}}\,. $$

4. Change variable $u=\Omega_{m,0}a'+\Omega_{r,0}$, $du=\Omega_{m,0}da'$, and when $a'=0\to u=\Omega_{r,0}$, $a'=a_{eq}\to u=2\Omega_{r,0}$. Then
$$a'=\frac{u-\Omega_{r,0}}{\Omega_{m,0}},\quad da'=\frac{du}{\Omega_{m,0}},$$
so
$$t_{eq}=\frac1{H_0\Omega_{m,0}^2}\int_{\Omega_{r,0}}^{2\Omega_{r,0}}
\!\!(u-\Omega_{r,0})u^{-\tfrac12}\,du\,. $$

5. Evaluate the integral:
\begin{align*}
\int(u-\Omega_{r,0})u^{-1/2}du
&=\int\!u^{1/2}du-\Omega_{r,0}\int\!u^{-1/2}du
=\frac{2}{3}u^{3/2}-2\Omega_{r,0}u^{1/2}\,,\\
\Bigl[\;\frac{2}{3}u^{3/2}-2\Omega_{r,0}u^{1/2}\Bigr]_{\Omega_{r,0}}^{2\Omega_{r,0}}
&=\frac{4-2\sqrt2}{3}\,\Omega_{r,0}^{3/2}\,.
\end{align*}

6. Hence
$$t_{eq}
=\frac1{H_0\Omega_{m,0}^2}\,\frac{4-2\sqrt2}{3}\,\Omega_{r,0}^{3/2}
=\frac{2(2-\sqrt2)}{3H_0}\,\frac{\Omega_{r,0}^{3/2}}{\Omega_{m,0}^2}\,. $$
